From: Gemini PDA Mainline Project <noreply@example.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 02:40:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 27/27] arm64: dts: mediatek: mt6797: add CMDQ GCE

Describe the MT6797 Global Command Engine as a 16-channel CMDQ mailbox
provider. Its register layout and unshifted command-buffer address format
match MT8173, so retain that compatible as the driver fallback.

Use only normal-world SPI 152. The downstream tree's second SPI is
reserved for its proprietary secure CMDQ path and is not part of the
upstream mailbox binding. The GCE is a standalone infrastructure block and
is safe to bind without consumers; multimedia clients will be added
separately after their event and subsystem-address contracts are verified.

Signed-off-by: Gemini PDA Mainline Project <noreply@example.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797.dtsi | 11 +++++++++++
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797.dtsi
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797.dtsi
@@ -5,6 +5,7 @@
  */
 
 #include <dt-bindings/clock/mt6797-clk.h>
+#include <dt-bindings/gce/mediatek,mt6797-gce.h>
 #include <dt-bindings/interrupt-controller/irq.h>
 #include <dt-bindings/interrupt-controller/arm-gic.h>
 #include <dt-bindings/pinctrl/mt6797-pinfunc.h>
@@ -287,6 +288,16 @@ m4u: iommu@10205000 {
 		status = "disabled";
 	};
 
+	gce: mailbox@10212000 {
+		compatible = "mediatek,mt6797-gce",
+			     "mediatek,mt8173-gce";
+		reg = <0 0x10212000 0 0x1000>;
+		interrupts = <GIC_SPI 152 IRQ_TYPE_LEVEL_LOW>;
+		clocks = <&infrasys CLK_INFRA_GCE>;
+		clock-names = "gce";
+		#mbox-cells = <2>;
+	};
+
 	uart0: serial@11002000 {
 		compatible = "mediatek,mt6797-uart",
 			     "mediatek,mt6577-uart";
-- 
